# AI-Tawala project map

Work in **~/Projects/AI-Tawala** (not the home directory) for all substantive changes.

## Runtimes

| Target | URL | Role |
|--------|-----|------|
| Browser Designer | http://localhost:5173 | `designer-web/` UI (Vite) |
| Designer dev API | http://localhost:3001 | JSON deploy, form runtime (`designer-web/server/`) |
| Java / Tomcat | http://localhost:8080 | Legacy webapp (Registration, DirtBowl parity tests) |

Start browser Designer: `cd designer-web && npm run dev`.

## Key directories

- `designer-web/` — browser Designer reimplementation (React + Express)
- `TawalaDesigner/Code/TAWALA/` — legacy C# WinForms Designer (authoritative UI/XML behavior)
- `TawalaWebapp-build1700/` — Java webapp source
- `docker/` — Tomcat/CSS containers for local 8080
- `Tawala_Key_Documents/` — owner specs, Designer UI documentation, project history
- `scripts/` — deploy and dev helpers (e.g. `deploy-dirtbowl-java.mjs`)

## Reference docs (read before guessing)

- `Tawala_Key_Documents/TAWALA_PROJECT_SUMMARY.md` — product/architecture overview
- `Tawala_Key_Documents/DESIGNER_*.md` — legacy Designer UI specs (menus, form items, canvas)
- `designer-web/README.md` — how to run and deploy from browser Designer

## Legacy vs new

- **Legacy Designer** = C# desktop app; owner documents it from screenshots on an old PC (Jan 2011 build in places).
- **Browser Designer** = `designer-web/`; goal is parity with legacy, not a new product design.
- **Design canvas ≫ Preview** — authoring UI is the product; Preview is a secondary check. Preview/runtime changes must not spill into Design components (Deploy may share server export paths). See `tawala-work-scopes.mdc`.
- **8080 runtime** = truth for end-user Registration HTML/CSS until browser Designer can express layouts natively.
